The paper deals with rate-matching for polar codes, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems (cs.IT and cs.COMM). The paper also discusses the use of bit-interleaved coded modulation (BICM), which is a technique commonly used in wireless communication systems (cs.SI). The paper proposes a low complexity algorithm for deriving an interleaver, which is a topic in discrete mathematics and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the computational complexity of the proposed scheme, which is a topic in computer networks and distributed systems (cs.NI).
